#ad I’m embracing little moments of Joy this January 😃 Whilst I’m confident that Wellwoman Max has my back with keeping my body healthy, I know that my mood can really slip in January, so here’s what you’ll find me doing to keep me feeling good …… 

1 Soaking up the last sliver of golden sunlight whilst really focusing on how good the sunshine feels on my face 
2 Leaving our fairy lights up so the house still feels cosy on the dark nights

4 Crunching the frozen leaves on a walk in my colourful trainers 
5 Scheduling in time to keep connected with my friends as January can be a lonely month with everyone hibernating.

Amsterdam Recommendations 🌷 Save this post if your hoping to visit🌷I’ve just got back from a glorious trip to Amsterdam with my friends and we found some great places to eat, shop, be inspired and sleep whilst we were out there which I think you’ll want to know about !! 🌷

1 @foam_amsterdam A photography gallery perfect for a little inspiration. They have different exhibitions that change every few months and it was €15 to visit as an adult

2 @nightkitchen.amsterdam We ate here on our last night as a special celebration meal for a fab trip. We shared a range of delicious dishes that they picked out for us to have as a family style dinner. Really interesting and tasty food !! 

3 @thefrozenfountain The most stunning art, design and interiors shop !! Although their price points are higher, I would say it’s well worth a trip even if you just walk around in awe of all the pieces like we did.

4 @sousamsterdam A great spot for lunch that we found whilst exploring “The 9 Streets” area of the city. 😋

5 Our @airbnb , the perfect base to call home whilst we were there. It was located in the north of Amsterdam more in the suburbs, but it was super easy to get into the Center using public transport and there was free parking right outside. DM me if you want the link. 

6 @mrstacksams A vegan pancake restaurant that was super tasty and way better value for your money compared to lots of pancake spots in the Center. I would really recommend the Dutch Apple pie stack !! 🍏🥞

7 @vandijkenko A huge antique and 2nd hand interiors shop in the north of the city. This place was amazing, but you might need a van to get all your goodies back home. Thanks to @ruthkaymorrison for giving me this recommendation 

8 @rongastrobarorientaldowntown 
The food we had here was super tasty !!! I would recommend booking as it was busy. We especially loved the crispy aubergine 🍆😋

9 @lauradolsvintage A beautiful vintage shop filled with gorgeous clothing, accessories and fabric. Lots of special pieces, and adorable vintage kids wear too. 

10 @fabriquedeslumieres was a magical art experience. We saw the Klimt show which was wonderful. I think a Salvador Dali show is coming soon.

I’ve been wanting a kilt for months !!! But it’s been so difficult to find a good quality one that fits me. I absolutely adored the Shrimps kilt and I’ve especially loved how @poppyalmond styled it up. I’ve seen lots of fabulous vintage kilts too, but they seem really rare above a size 18/20. So I thought that buying two and joining them together might be the best way for me to get one into my wardrobe. I found these vintage pure wool skirts for £15 each and with the addiction of the buckles for £8 it made the skirt £38, which actually feels like a bargain for fabric of this quality. I’m SO pleased with how it’s turned out !!! I really think this is a classic I’ll have in my wardrobe for years !! What do you think ??? ❤️🖤💚💙🤎

Make a flower choker with me 🌸 I’ve been seeing lots of floral neck ties recently so thought I would make my own using a technique I learnt a few years ago. It’s pretty simple to do and means you could make a flower to match any of your outfits in a colour of your choice 🌸 I made a matching rouleau tie in the same fabric to attach the flower to but you could easily use a ribbon or an existing choker 🎀 I’d love to see your creations if you make one. Yay for INCLUSION !!! Although we are far from perfection, I really wanted to point out @coggles for their inclusion of me, a plus size person in their pr marketing. I have been watching lots of my fabulous fashion peers showcasing Coggles over the past few months and I have been hoping to work with them too, however as a plus size influencer I’m often overlooked by premium and designer fashion. Yes I’m still limited by what I can wear from Coggles, but some of their brands @ganni and @stinegoyastudio in particular have started to make moves towards expanding their size range, and of course gorgeous bags and accessories are open to all. I like to point out all progress because we’re only going to get there through lots of little things adding up to bigger things. So if you can please make it clear to premium brands that you appreciate their size inclusive efforts and that you want to see more 😁 we are getting somewhere finally !!

Upsize a denim maxi skirt with me 💫 I am obsessed with the idea of upsizing !! I’ve grown impatient with waiting for trend pieces to be available in my size and where possible I love to reuse existing clothes. An up-size upcycle is the perfect task to tick both of those boxes. AD What a stunning week ❤️ Cruising through the Mediterranean with my gorgeous pal @rubyrare onboard the @virginvoyages Valiant Lady ❤️ We travelled with @trendingtravel who are a travel agency with some incredible deals on fabulous breaks just like this one !! 

Our itinerary looked like this -

Ad I recently enjoyed a few days of solo travel in Barcelona and here’s what I learnt about exploring on your own …. 
1. Fuel yourself well!! I started my days with a filling and healthy breakfast and a Wellwoman Energy as I knew I had a full day ahead 
2. Take slow moments. Pack a sketchbook and pens so you can really take the time to observe the space you’re in. Don’t worry, it's just for you, you don’t need to be Van Gogh 
3. Do the things YOU love !! This might seem obvious, but don’t feel the need to just do what the guide book tells you. Hunt out activities you love, for me that’s flea markets & haberdashery’s. 
4. Record your day. I wanted to stay present in the day, so rather than texting my friends and family what I was up to, I took lots of quick snaps and videos to show them afterwards. 
5. Look up, look down, look all around. Take the time to really take in this different space that you're in. I fell in love with these floral patterns on the Barcelona streets, something I could have easily just walked over and missed. I love Wellwoman Energy on days like this because it’s so easy to travel with. I am SO excited that @joanieclothing have extended their size range to go up to a UK26. As a uk size 24 and occasionally size 26 I wanted to try out a range of their pieces to tell you how they fit. 
First up is this Prairie style dress from their recent collaboration with Laura Ashley. I will be keeping the size 26 as I found the size 24 too tight over my bust. The neckline and cuffs felt like they fitted well and I loved the length. Ask away if you have more questions. 
For reference my measurements are:
Bust 140cm
Waist 123cm
Hip 146cm

Ad - Pr samples

Part 2 of my @joanieclothing try on 💚 After I saw that Joanie had extended their size range up to a UK26 I knew I would be welcoming some great retro and vintage inspired prints into my wardrobe 🍀 I love a retro floral and in an all over co-ord moment it’s even better. This outfit is really comfortable as each piece has stretch in it. The top is a classic t-shirt kind of jersey and I got this in a XXL (24-26). This has a short zip at the back neck so you can avoid messing up your makeup when you put it on. It fits well on the body but I would quite like it to have slightly slimmer sleeves. The size 24 fit me best in the trousers, these are in a heavier weight jersey and are way more comfortable than I was expecting, I really like this style. The cardigan is an easy chuck-on style and finishes the outfit off perfectly also in a size XXL (24-26). I know these pieces will get a lot of wears this winter !!! 🍀🍀🍀

Ad - pr samples

Taking my @karenmabon sea birds silk robe back to its natural habitat 🌊🐧🐚🦀🪸🪨 

Pr sample

Part 3 of my @joanieclothing try on 🧡 I started off with this incredible printed shirt. I love the print, the colour palette and they statement collar but I found the sleeves were a little too wide. This is often one of the places that seems to get too big when patterns are graded so I’m guessing this is what has happened here. That an maybe I have slim wrists for my size ? I know much of my weight is distributed on my torso. It’s quite an easy fix though as I should just be able to move the buttons on the cuffs. I love the stretch velvet fabric quality of the skirt and waistcoat. I think I will go with a 24 in the skirt and a 26 in the waistcoat. The skirt in the size 24 looks a good length on me and fit well. I love that it’s got pockets !! The waistcoat is harder to decide on sizing as both the 24 and 26 fit but I felt like the 24 might end up gaping too much. There is a strap on the waist at the back that means you can cinch it in slightly making the 26 fit better :) 

Overall I think that if you have a bigger bust for your size you might need to size up in Joanie, but with everything else I think you are ok in your usual size. They also seem to use a lot of fabrics with stretch so they are comfortable and also for a little bit of fit flexibility whilst still giving a clean look. 

Please ask me any questions if you have more fit queries 😁

Another project that’s been living in my mind for years that I’m finally making !!! We live in a rented house so improvements are limited, but I’m forever determined to make the space feel designed and feel like me. Our hallway is currently pretty empty and it feels lifeless, I want to bring warmer lighting from a lamp and more colour into the space. I also really want a place I can put a candle so I can make it smell cosy and welcoming. For all those reasons I’m making a shelf / cover for our radiator. I wanted it to have curved lines, colour and a bit of drama and I think we’re on the right path. I’m so excited to get this painted and on the wall ready to decorate for Christmas time !! This craft workshop was part of the many classes and workshops offered free to residents who rent at Coppermaker Square. Such a wholesome way to spend an evening and focus on your own wellness, and what a great way to meet your neighbours!

There is really something for everyone – so …. when can we move in?

AD 18+ Frosted Rosemary Paloma Recipe ❄️ Add a zing to your Christmas shopping list with our 100% pure Pink Grapefruit Juice—because why settle for ordinary when you can go tangy and invigorating? ✨😏
 
Ingredients:
Ice 🧊
50ml Tequila Blanco 😎
10ml Rosemary Syrup 🌹
10ml Fresh Lime Juice 😏
60ml Tropicana Pink Grapefruit Juice 🧃
Soda Water 💧
 
Garnish:
A pinch of coarse sea salt 🧂
Lime wedge 🙌
Slice of Pink Grapefruit 😍
Rosemary Syrup 😉
 Equal parts sugar and water (using a milk jug as a measurement) 👏
3 fresh sprigs of rosemary 👌
 
Combine the sugar, water, and rosemary in a pan and bring to a boil until the sugar is dissolved making sure not to burn. Simmer on a low heat for 5 mins. Take off the hob, let it cool completely, and remove the rosemary. Then it’s ready to use 🌲
 
Enjoy 🍹
